use of Flanders]]\n[[Category:Regents of England]]\n[[Category:William the Conqueror]]\n", "name_user": "AndrewCumberland12", "label": "safe", "comment": "Inserted correct biographical inflation of Matilda and also background of what Flanders was of strategic importance at the time.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matilda_of_Flanders"}
{"title_page": "Mesochelydia", "text_new": "{{Automatic taxobox\n| fossil_range = {{fossilrange|Early Jurassic|Present}}\n| image = Kayentachelys_NT.jpg\n| image_caption = ''[[Kayentachelys]]\n| taxon = Mesochelydia\n| authority = Joyce, 2017\n| subdivision_ranks = Subgroupings\n| subdivision = * \u2020''[[Condorchelys]]''\n* \u2020''[[Eileanchelys]]''\n* \u2020''[[Heckerochelys]]''\n* \u2020''[[Indochelys]]''\n* \u2020''[[Kayentachelys]]''\n* [[Perichelydia]]\n}}\n'''Mesochelydia''' (from [[Greek language|Greek]] ''mesos'' \"middle\" and ''chelys'' \"turtle\") is a clade of stem-turtles, more inclusive than [[Perichelydia]], but less than [[Testudinata]]. The clade is known from the Early Jurassic to the Present.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Joyce|first=Walter G.|date=April 2017|title=A Review of the Fossil Record of Basal Mesozoic Turtles|url=https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/A-Review-of-the-Fossil-Record-of-Basal-Mesozoic-Joyce/845585d63ffdc4c2d08c2c5132bc76db0a1b578e|journal=Bulletin of the Peabody Museum of Natural History|language=en|volume=58|issue=1|pages=65\u2013113|doi=10.3374/014.058.0105|issn=0079-032X|via=}}</ref> The ancestral condition for Mesochelydia is thought to be aquatic, as opposed to terrestrial for Testudinata.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sterli|first=Juliana|last2=de la Fuente|first2=Marcelo S.|last3=Rougier|first3=Guillermo W.|date=2018-07-04|title=New remains of Condorchelys antiqua (Testudinata) from the Early-Middle Jurassic of Patagonia: anatomy, phylogeny, and paedomorphosis in the early evolution of turtles|journal=Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology|language=en|volume=38|issue=4|pages=(1)\u2013(17)|doi=10.1080/02724634.2018.1480112|issn=0272-4634}}</ref> They are distinguished from more basal Testudinatans by the presence of the following characters: strap like pectoral girdle, supramarginals absent, reduced posterior entoplastral process, eleven pairs of peripherals, elongate processus interfenestralis, paired basioccipital tubercles, fully formed [[cavum tympani]] and antrum postoticum, single [[vomer]], confluent external [[nares]], [[Lacrimal bone|lacrimals]] and [[supratemporal]]s absent.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Taxonomy ==\n\n* ''[[Condorchelys]]'' <small>Sterli, 2008</small> [[Ca\u00f1ad\u00f3n Asfalto Formation]], [[Middle Jurassic]], Argentina\n* ''[[Eileanchelys]]'' <small>Anquetin et al. 2009</small> [[Kilmaluag Formation]], [[Bathonian]], Scotland\n* ''[[Heckerochelys]]'' <small>Sukhanov, 2006</small><ref>V. B. Sukhanov. 2006. An archaic turtle, Heckerochelys romani gen. et sp. nov. from the Middle Jurassic of Moscow region, Russia. ''Fossil Turtle Research'' '''1''':112-118</ref>  [[Moskvoretskaya Formation]], Bathonian, Russia\n* ''[[Indochelys]]'' <small>Datta et al, 2000</small><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Datta|first=P.M.|last2=Manna|first2=P.|last3=Ghosh|first3=S.C.|last4=Das|first4=D. P.|date=April 2000|title=The First Jurassic turtle from India|journal=Palaeontology|volume=43|issue=1|pages=99\u2013109|doi=10.1111/1475-4983.00120|issn=0031-0239}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Joyce|first=Walter G.|last2=Bandyopadhyay|first2=Saswati|date=2020-02-11|title=A reevaluation of the basal turtle Indochelys spatulata from the Early\u2013Middle Jurassic (Toarcian\u2013Aalenian) of India, with descriptions of new material|journal=PeerJ|volume=8|pages=e8542|doi=10.7717/peerj.8542|pmid=32095362|pmc=7020818|issn=2167-8359}}</ref> [[Kota Formation]], [[Toarcian]], India\n* ''[[Kayentachelys]]'' <small>Gaffney et al. 1987</small> [[Kayenta Formation]], [[Sinemurian]], United States \n*[[Perichelydia]] <small>Joyce, 2017</small> Middle Jurassic-Present, Worldwide\n\nAdditionally, an indeterminate basal non-Perichelydian Mesochelydian taxon is known from the [[Early Cretaceous]] [[Batylykh Formation]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Skutschas|first=Pavel P.|last2=Markova|first2=Valentina D.|last3=Kolchanov|first3=Veniamin V.|last4=Averianov|first4=Alexander O.|last5=Martin|first5=Thomas|last6=Schellhorn|first6=Rico|last7=Kolosov|first7=Petr N.|last8=Grigoriev|first8=Dmitry V.|last9=Vitenko|first9=Dmitry D.|last10=Obraztsova|first10=Ekaterina M.|last11=Danilov|first11=Igor G.|date=February 2020|title=Basal turtle material from the Lower Cretaceous of Yakutia (Russia) filling the gap in the Asian record|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S019566711930134X|journal=Cretaceous Research|language=en|volume=106|pages=104186|doi=10.1016/j.cretres.2019.07.016}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Pantestudines}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q68334453}}\n\n[[Category:Testudinata]]\n", "text_old": "{{Automatic taxobox\n| fossil_range = {{fossilrange|Early Jurassic|Present}}\n| image = Kayentachelys_NT.jpg\n| image_caption = ''[[Kayentachelys]]\n| taxon = Mesochelydia\n| authority = Joyce, 2017\n| subdivision_ranks = Subgroupings\n| subdivision = * \u2020''[[Condorchelys]]''\n* \u2020''[[Eileanchelys]]''\n* \u2020''[[Heckerochelys]]''\n* \u2020''[[Indochelys]]''\n* \u2020''[[Kayentachelys]]''\n* [[Perichelydia]]\n}}\n'''Mesochelydia ('''from [[Greek language|Greek]] ''mesos'' \"middle\" and ''chelys'' \"turtle\") is a clade of stem-turtles, more inclusive than [[Perichelydia]], but less than [[Testudinata]]. The clade is known from the Early Jurassic to the Present.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Joyce|first=Walter G.|date=April 2017|title=A Review of the Fossil Record of Basal Mesozoic Turtles|url=https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/A-Review-of-the-Fossil-Record-of-Basal-Mesozoic-Joyce/845585d63ffdc4c2d08c2c5132bc76db0a1b578e|journal=Bulletin of the Peabody Museum of Natural History|language=en|volume=58|issue=1|pages=65\u2013113|doi=10.3374/014.058.0105|issn=0079-032X|via=}}</ref> The ancestral condition for Mesochelydia is thought to be aquatic, as opposed to terrestrial for Testudinata.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sterli|first=Juliana|last2=de la Fuente|first2=Marcelo S.|last3=Rougier|first3=Guillermo W.|date=2018-07-04|title=New remains of Condorchelys antiqua (Testudinata) from the Early-Middle Jurassic of Patagonia: anatomy, phylogeny, and paedomorphosis in the early evolution of turtles|journal=Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology|language=en|volume=38|issue=4|pages=(1)\u2013(17)|doi=10.1080/02724634.2018.1480112|issn=0272-4634}}</ref> They are distinguished from more basal Testudinatans by the presence of the following characters: strap like pectoral girdle, supramarginals absent, reduced posterior entoplastral process, eleven pairs of peripherals, elongate processus interfenestralis, paired basioccipital tubercles, fully formed [[cavum tympani]] and antrum postoticum, single [[vomer]], confluent external [[nares]], [[Lacrimal bone|lacrimals]] and [[supratemporal]]s absent.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Taxonomy ==\n\n* ''[[Condorchelys]]'' <small>Sterli, 2008</small> [[Ca\u00f1ad\u00f3n Asfalto Formation]], [[Middle Jurassic]], Argentina\n* ''[[Eileanchelys]]'' <small>Anquetin et al. 2009</small> [[Kilmaluag Formation]], [[Bathonian]], Scotland\n* ''[[Heckerochelys]]'' <small>Sukhanov, 2006</small><ref>V. B. Sukhanov. 2006. An archaic turtle, Heckerochelys romani gen. et sp. nov. from the Middle Jurassic of Moscow region, Russia. ''Fossil Turtle Research'' '''1''':112-118</ref>  [[Moskvoretskaya Formation]], Bathonian, Russia\n* ''[[Indochelys]]'' <small>Datta et al, 2000</small><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Datta|first=P.M.|last2=Manna|first2=P.|last3=Ghosh|first3=S.C.|last4=Das|first4=D. P.|date=April 2000|title=The First Jurassic turtle from India|journal=Palaeontology|volume=43|issue=1|pages=99\u2013109|doi=10.1111/1475-4983.00120|issn=0031-0239}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Joyce|first=Walter G.|last2=Bandyopadhyay|first2=Saswati|date=2020-02-11|title=A reevaluation of the basal turtle Indochelys spatulata from the Early\u2013Middle Jurassic (Toarcian\u2013Aalenian) of India, with descriptions of new material|journal=PeerJ|volume=8|pages=e8542|doi=10.7717/peerj.8542|pmid=32095362|pmc=7020818|issn=2167-8359}}</ref> [[Kota Formation]], [[Toarcian]], India\n* ''[[Kayentachelys]]'' <small>Gaffney et al. 1987</small> [[Kayenta Formation]], [[Sinemurian]], United States \n*[[Perichelydia]] <small>Joyce, 2017</small> Middle Jurassic-Present, Worldwide\n\nAdditionally, an indeterminate basal non-Perichelydian Mesochelydian taxon is known from the [[Early Cretaceous]] [[Batylykh Formation]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Skutschas|first=Pavel P.|last2=Markova|first2=Valentina D.|last3=Kolchanov|first3=Veniamin V.|last4=Averianov|first4=Alexander O.|last5=Martin|first5=Thomas|last6=Schellhorn|first6=Rico|last7=Kolosov|first7=Petr N.|last8=Grigoriev|first8=Dmitry V.|last9=Vitenko|first9=Dmitry D.|last10=Obraztsova|first10=Ekaterina M.|last11=Danilov|first11=Igor G.|date=February 2020|title=Basal turtle material from the Lower Cretaceous of Yakutia (Russia) filling the gap in the Asian record|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S019566711930134X|journal=Cretaceous Research|language=en|volume=106|pages=104186|doi=10.1016/j.cretres.2019.07.016}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Pantestudines}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q68334453}}\n\n[[Category:Testudinata]]\n", "name_user": "Hemiauchenia", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mesochelydia"}
